The paper deals with the problem of channel estimation in massive MIMO systems using compressive sensing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also deals with the special structure of the channel, which is a form of sparsity, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) another likely category. The paper also discusses the potential benefits of small training overhead, which is related to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new algorithm, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
